Inductive argument Inductive argument There are two types of inductive argument: 1) Strong inductive argument or strong argument. 2) Weak inductive argument or weak argument. Strong argument Strong argument - is a type of inductive argument such that the premises are assumed true, it is improbable for the conclusion to be false.
Strong argument - the conclusion follows probably from the premises. (premises) (conclusion) argument strong argument (premises) conclusion strong inductive argument Example 1 Most film actresses are beautiful. Rosa is a film actress. Therefore, Rosa is probably beautiful. Most film actresses are beautiful Rosa is a film actress premises premises
